This project introduces a governed authoring layer for Protocol-Governed Systems in which:

- Human intent is expressed conversationally
- A compiler-projected protocol cognition substrate (PPS) grounds all reasoning
- Artifacts are generated through structured templates, not freeform generation
- Human approval is required before compiler validation
- The compiler remains the sole authority on admissibility

The LLM converses. The compiler admits. The protocol governs.

Extensibility is achieved by governed authoring, not manual artifact construction.
